# =============================================================================
# CARD: Push the Civil Rights Act
# =============================================================================

@lbj_cr_push_cra
title: The Civil Rights Act
is-card: true
card-image: img/cra_card.png
tags: lbj_cr_card
view-if: lbj_ev_cra64 = 0 and lbj_year <= 1964
max-visits: 3

Kennedy put it before Congress. It is going nowhere. The Southern senators have their filibuster positions picked out. They have been preparing for this moment for a decade.

You have the votes, maybe, if you work every phone in this building. You have Russell. You have Dirksen on the Republican side, if you can make him feel like a statesman rather than a collaborator.

What you don't have is time. The movement is not going to wait for parliamentary procedure.

- @lbj_cr_push_cra_hard: Push hard. Call every senator personally. This is your legacy.
- @lbj_cr_push_cra_moderate: Work the middle. Find the version that can pass.
- @lbj_cr_push_cra_delay: Focus on other priorities first. The Act can wait.

@lbj_cr_push_cra_hard
title: The Full Push
on-arrival: lbj_capital -= 18; lbj_dixiecrats -= 12; lbj_liberals += 8; lbj_labor += 5; lbj_south_backlash += 10; lbj_racial_tension -= 8; lbj_credibility += 5

You call forty-three senators in seventy-two hours. You are not above begging. You have never been above begging.

Russell tells you you're making a mistake. You tell him history is going to prove you right, and he says history isn't running for anything in 1964. You say you are.

The bill is stronger for the fight. Your southern support is not.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

@lbj_cr_push_cra_moderate
title: The Art of the Possible
on-arrival: lbj_capital -= 10; lbj_dixiecrats -= 6; lbj_liberals += 4; lbj_south_backlash += 6; lbj_racial_tension -= 4; lbj_credibility += 2

Compromise is not a dirty word. You have been compromising since you were a county administrator.

The bill that emerges is not perfect. The movement will not say it is perfect. But it will be law. It will have teeth. It will be something.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

@lbj_cr_push_cra_delay
title: Not Yet
on-arrival: lbj_liberals -= 8; lbj_racial_tension += 6; lbj_credibility -= 4; lbj_jfk_shadow += 8

Kennedy promised it. You are promising it. The difference between a promise and a bill is, at the moment, everything.

The movement does not forget. You are building a tab you will eventually have to pay.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

# =============================================================================
# CARD: King at the White House
# =============================================================================

@lbj_cr_king_meeting
title: Dr. King
is-card: true
card-image: img/king_card.png
tags: lbj_cr_card
max-visits: 4

He is not easy to be in a room with. That is not a complaint — easy men do not lead movements.

He has that quality of knowing he is on the right side of history and knowing you know it too, and watching you calculate the political cost anyway. It should make you feel small. It does make you feel small. You do not show it.

He wants more than you have given. He always wants more. That is his job.

- @lbj_cr_king_ally: Make him an ally. Give him access and make it real.
- @lbj_cr_king_arm: Keep him at arm's length. Useful, not intimate.
- @lbj_cr_king_fbi: Let Hoover do what Hoover does.

@lbj_cr_king_ally
title: An Alliance
on-arrival: lbj_liberals += 7; lbj_racial_tension -= 5; lbj_cr_progress += 1; lbj_dixiecrats -= 4; lbj_south_backlash += 5; lbj_capital -= 8

You give him your direct number. You mean it when you say it. He will call it.

The Southern press will have a field day. Russell will give you a look across the Senate chamber that contains an entire editorial.

You have needed worse enemies.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

@lbj_cr_king_arm
title: Managed Distance
on-arrival: lbj_liberals += 2; lbj_racial_tension -= 2; lbj_jfk_shadow += 3

Productive meeting. Warm but not effusive. You commit to the process without committing to specifics.

He leaves knowing he hasn't gotten what he came for. You both know it. These meetings have a grammar of their own.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

@lbj_cr_king_fbi
title: Hoover's Files
on-arrival: lbj_south_backlash -= 3; lbj_liberals -= 10; lbj_credibility -= 6; lbj_coup += 3; lbj_paranoia += 4

Hoover has been watching King for years. The files exist. The surveillance is ongoing.

You don't order anything. You simply don't order it stopped. There is a difference. There is always a difference. You are not sure, at 2 a.m., that anyone else can see it.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

# =============================================================================
# CARD: Freedom Summer / Mississippi Burning
# =============================================================================

@lbj_cr_freedom_summer
title: Mississippi
is-card: true
card-image: img/mississippi_card.png
tags: lbj_cr_card
view-if: lbj_year = 1964
max-visits: 1

Three young men are missing in Mississippi. Chaney, Goodman, Schwerner. Everyone knows what happened. Nobody in Mississippi is in any hurry to find them.

The FBI is involved, technically. J. Edgar Hoover is involved the way Hoover is involved in things — meaning he is gathering information, and that information is going into files, and the files are going places that are not courts of law.

The country is watching. The cameras are down there. The question is what you say.

- @lbj_cr_fs_federal: Send federal resources. Make it a federal case.
- @lbj_cr_fs_rhetoric: Speak forcefully. Let the system work.
- @lbj_cr_fs_quiet: Handle it quietly. Don't escalate.

@lbj_cr_fs_federal
title: Federal Power
on-arrival: lbj_capital -= 12; lbj_dixiecrats -= 14; lbj_liberals += 9; lbj_racial_tension -= 6; lbj_unity += 3; lbj_south_backlash += 12; lbj_credibility += 4

You send every available agent. You call the governor directly and you are not polite about it.

The bodies are found in August. The country mourns. Mississippi does not change overnight, but the calculus has shifted — now everyone knows the federal government means it.

Your southern colleagues do not forgive this. You did not expect them to.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

@lbj_cr_fs_rhetoric
title: Moral Clarity
on-arrival: lbj_credibility += 2; lbj_liberals += 4; lbj_racial_tension -= 2; lbj_capital -= 3

You give a speech. It is a good speech. Words matter.

The bodies are found in August. The speech is in the record. The families bury their sons.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

@lbj_cr_fs_quiet
title: Back Channels
on-arrival: lbj_dixiecrats += 3; lbj_liberals -= 8; lbj_credibility -= 5; lbj_racial_tension += 4; lbj_jfk_shadow += 5

You make calls. Quiet ones. You lean on the governor through intermediaries.

The bodies are found in August. You are not associated with finding them. You are not associated with anything.

The movement notices. They are keeping score.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

# =============================================================================
# CARD: The Voting Rights Act
# =============================================================================

@lbj_cr_vra
title: Selma
is-card: true
card-image: img/selma_card.png
tags: lbj_cr_card
view-if: lbj_ev_cra64 = 1 and lbj_year >= 1965
max-visits: 2

The images from the Edmund Pettus Bridge are on every television in America. State troopers. Clubs. Tear gas. People in their Sunday best being beaten on a bridge named for a Klan grand wizard.

You have a decision. The Voting Rights Act has been sitting in committee.

You know what you're going to do. You have known since you watched the footage at 11 o'clock last night, alone in the residence, with the sound turned down. The question is how you do it.

- @lbj_cr_vra_congress: Address a joint session of Congress. Make it historic.
- @lbj_cr_vra_executive: Move by executive order where possible. Faster.
- @lbj_cr_vra_wait: Wait for calmer political conditions.

@lbj_cr_vra_congress
title: We Shall Overcome
on-arrival: lbj_ev_vra65 = 1; lbj_cr_progress += 2; lbj_capital -= 20; lbj_dixiecrats -= 18; lbj_liberals += 12; lbj_unity += 6; lbj_south_backlash += 16; lbj_racial_tension -= 12; lbj_credibility += 8; lbj_jfk_shadow -= 10

*"We shall overcome."*

You say it. You, Lyndon Baines Johnson of Johnson City, Texas, son of the Hill Country, say those words to a joint session of Congress and to forty million people watching at home. You let the pause sit before you say it, so everyone knows you know what you're saying.

Forty years from now, they will teach this speech in schools.

Tonight, Russell leaves without speaking to you.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

@lbj_cr_vra_executive
title: Executive Action
on-arrival: lbj_ev_vra65 = 1; lbj_cr_progress += 1; lbj_capital -= 10; lbj_dixiecrats -= 8; lbj_liberals += 6; lbj_racial_tension -= 7; lbj_south_backlash += 8

You push what you can push through existing authority and lean hard on Congress for the rest. It passes, somewhat quieter than it might have.

Quieter, perhaps, than it should have been. The moment called for more than you gave it.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

@lbj_cr_vra_wait
title: Not the Right Moment
on-arrival: lbj_liberals -= 12; lbj_racial_tension += 9; lbj_credibility -= 7; lbj_jfk_shadow += 10; lbj_capital += 5

The moment passes. Moments always pass.

The bill will come back. The Selma footage will air again, on anniversaries, in documentaries. People will remember when it happened and they will remember that you waited.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

