# SCRIPTED EVENT: Watts, August 1965
# =============================================================================

@lbj_ev_watts_trigger
title: Los Angeles Burns
is-card: true
card-image: img/watts_card.png
on-arrival: lbj_ev_watts = 1; lbj_racial_tension += 18; lbj_unity -= 8; lbj_far_right += 8; lbj_south_backlash += 6
go-to: lbj_ev_watts_scene

@lbj_ev_watts_scene
title: Watts
new-page: true

The Voting Rights Act is six days old.

Watts is on fire. Not metaphorically. Thirty-four people will die. More than a thousand will be injured. The National Guard is deploying into an American city that looks, on the news footage, like a war zone.

You have just signed the most important civil rights legislation in a century. And the cities are burning.

You are told — by advisors who are very careful about how they say it — that these are not the same people who marched in Selma. This is frustration, poverty, police brutality that has nothing to do with voting rights and everything to do with the Watts in which people actually live.

You know they are right. You know this is what you have been trying to address with the Great Society programs. You also know that the footage is on television, and it is going to mean something to voters that it did not mean before.

- @lbj_ev_watts_respond_force: Deploy National Guard. Restore order first.
- @lbj_ev_watts_respond_understand: Address the root causes publicly.
- @lbj_ev_watts_respond_kerner: Commission a study. Understand before acting.

@lbj_ev_watts_respond_force
title: Order First
on-arrival: lbj_racial_tension -= 8; lbj_unity += 4; lbj_liberals -= 7; lbj_far_right -= 4; lbj_south_backlash -= 3

Order is restored. The fires go out. You are resolute in the press.

The underlying conditions that caused Watts are unchanged. You know this. The press does not particularly want to discuss this. The far right does not believe this.

There will be other Watts.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

@lbj_ev_watts_respond_understand
title: The Deeper Fire
on-arrival: lbj_racial_tension -= 4; lbj_liberals += 5; lbj_far_right += 5; lbj_unity -= 3; lbj_gs_progress += 1

You speak about poverty, about housing, about the unfinished work of the Great Society. You are not wrong. You will be accused of excusing lawlessness. You do not excuse it. You explain it.

The distinction will be debated for decades. In the meantime, you find funding for Watts.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

@lbj_ev_watts_respond_kerner
title: Commission
on-arrival: lbj_capital -= 5; lbj_racial_tension -= 3; lbj_liberals += 3

You create a commission. Governor Kerner of Illinois will chair it.

In two years, it will tell you what you already know: America is moving toward two societies, separate and unequal. The report will be a bestseller. Congress will do almost nothing about it.

For now, it buys time and demonstrates seriousness.

- @lbj_main_hand: Back to the Oval Office

